# Environment Configuration Example

## Development Environment
NODE_ENV=development
API_URL=http://localhost:3001
DEBUG=true

## Production Environment
NODE_ENV=production
API_URL=https://api.tapel.com
DEBUG=false

## Add to .env file
Create a `.env` file in the root directory with environment-specific variables:

```
# API Configuration
VITE_API_URL=https://api.tapel.com
VITE_API_KEY=your_api_key_here

# App Configuration
VITE_APP_NAME=TAPEL
VITE_APP_VERSION=1.0.0

# Feature Flags
VITE_ENABLE_NOTIFICATIONS=true
VITE_ENABLE_ANALYTICS=true

# Third-party Services
VITE_GOOGLE_ANALYTICS_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX
```

## Usage in Code

```javascript
const apiUrl = process.env.VITE_API_URL;
const apiKey = process.env.VITE_API_KEY;
```

## Build-time Variables

These will be replaced during build:
- Development: `npm start` uses development values
- Production: `npm run build` uses production values
